jei.steamworld.grinder.description=The Steam Grinder is capable of grinding ores and ingots down to their dust counterparts.\nUpgrades increase the production.
jei.steamworld.furnace.description=The Steam Furnace works just like a regular furnace, but uses the power of steam instead.\nUpgrades increase the efficiency.
jei.steamworld.fisher.description=The Fisher automatically catches fish, underwater treasure and... Sunken junk. It does need to be adjacent to water in order to work.\nUpgrades increase the efficiency.
jei.steamworld.farmer.description=The Farmer harvest your nearby crops and tries to plant back the seeds.\nUpgrades increase the production.
jei.steamworld.lumber.description=The Lumberjack chops down logs and leaves that are nearby and tries to place back saplings. Be warned, as it does not discriminate against logs and leaves you've placed yourself!\nUpgrades increase the production.
jei.steamworld.fertilizer.description=The Fertilizer keeps nearby crops and plants healthy with the help of bonemeal.\nUpgrades increase the rate.
jei.steamworld.generator.description=The Steam Generator uses fuel to heat up water, producing steam. This steam can then be used to power steam-based machines.\nUpgrades increase the efficiency and capacity.
jei.steamworld.generator_nether.description=The Nether Steam Generator, unlike other Steam Generators, does not need fuel. It uses the Nether's ever-lasting heat instead. However, it is very slow in comparison.
jei.steamworld.drain.description=The Drain absorbs nearby fluids into the fluid system. It has a 1000mb buffer.\nTip: Use this in an enclosed area together with the faucet to create a storage tank.
jei.steamworld.faucet.description=The Faucet puts fluids out of the fluid system into the world. It has a 1000mb buffer.\nTip: Use this in an enclosed area together with the drain to create a storage tank.
jei.steamworld.fluid_controller.description=The Fluid Controller pumps liquids from a pipe-system on one side to one on the other. It has a small buffer and can be controlled with redstone, of which the behaviour can be changed by right-clicking it.\nUpgrades increase the efficiency and buffer size.
jei.steamworld.assembler.description=The Steam Assembler is used to assemble (or otherwise called "craft") various high-grade items that are not possible to craft by hand.
jei.steamworld.experience_machine.description=The Experience Machine does what it says on the tin: It takes in steam and uses it to create experience.\nUpgrades increase the efficiency.
jei.steamworld.miner.description=The Ender Miner mines ores and blocks from a semi-existant plane on the EnderNet. Let's not sweat the details about this, though.\nUpgrades increase the efficiency and max drill tier.\nThe Miner can not use a drill of the same tier or higher.
jei.steamworld.accelerator.description=The Nether Accelerator speeds up nearby Nether Steam Generators slightly, but at a cost...
jei.steamworld.energy.description=The Dynamo and Electric Steam Generator allow Steam to be converted to Redstone Flux and back respectively.

